Thresholding: From Gimp to Python

In image processing, thresholding is a technique whereby each pixel in an image is changed to make the image easier to analyze. Typically, it is the first stage in segmenting images, and is best employed on images with low noise level and higher intra-class variance (pixels from a particular group have closer intensities than pixels from another group). Since these two restrictions heavily apply to our problem, thesholding and masking on their own are an ill-posed technique.

Nevertheless, thresholding techniques remain highly valuable in maximizing contrast even in noisy images. Originally, our team manually increased pixel contrast in Gimp GNU, which is a free alternative to Adobe photoshop for image manipulation.

Naturally, this process involves much manual intervention for each altered image, so a function was written in Python to automatically handle large sets of images. Since .jpg files are essentially an array of RGB intensity values, all that is needed to be done is to scale each value appropriately.

Python Implementation

Main Function 

from PIL import Image
import numpy as np
from IPython.display import  display
# Color Leveling Function 
def colorLeveling(a, low=200, high=255):
    """
    :param a: image array, usually 3d array
    :param low: lower threshold; default is 200
    :param high: higher threshold; default is 255
    :return: color leveled array; same shape as original image 
    """
    leveling = lambda t:  min(high, max(0, (t - low) * high / (high - low)))
    vfunc = np.vectorize(leveling)
    new_a = vfunc(a)
    return new_a.astype(np.uint8)

Some Examples 

image = Image.open('sample_image.jpg')
display(image)
# convert image to array
image_arr = np.array(image)

image_arr_lvl = colorLeveling(image_arr, low=100, high=255)
image_lvl = Image.fromarray(image_arr_lvl)
display(image_lvl)

See how Color Leveling enhances colorful stripes

image_moire = Image.open('sample_moire_image.jpg')
display(image_moire)
image_moire_arr = np.array(image_moire)
image_moire_arr_lvl = colorLeveling(image_moire_arr, low=100, high=255)
image_moire_lvl = Image.fromarray(image_moire_arr_lvl)
display(image_moire_lvl)
